-- Cocaine Worth 4.8 Billion Yen Found on Japan Beach, Asahi
-- B y   T e r j e   L a n g e l a n d   a n d   M a r c o   L u i
-- 2013-11-21T05:23:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-11-21/cocaine-worth-4-8-billion-yen-found-on-japan-beach-asahi.html
Four backpacks stuffed with cocaine
worth 4.8 billion yen ($48 million) were found on a beach in
 Japan , the biggest amount ever discovered in the country, local
media reported.  The backpacks, containing 80 kilograms (176 pounds) of the
drug wrapped in waterproof tape, were found by local residents
in Yokosuka city on Nov. 19, the Asahi newspaper reported,
citing local police. The find is the biggest by value in Japan,
public broadcaster NHK said.  Yokosuka, home to a U.S. Navy base, is about 50 kilometers
(31 miles) south of  Tokyo .  To contact the reporters on this story:
Terje Langeland in Tokyo at 
